adjectives\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | '''th'''\n| broad\n| {{IPA|/h/}}\n| {{lang|ga|thaisce}} {{IPA|/\u02c8ha\u0283c\u0259/}} \"treasure\" (lenited), {{lang|ga|athair}} {{IPA|/\u02c8ah\u0259\u027e\u02b2/}} \"father\"\n|-\n| slender\n| {{IPA|/h/}}<br />{{IPA|/\u00e7/}} before {{IPA|/a\u02d0-, o\u02d0-, u\u02d0-/}}, usually from lenition\n| {{lang|ga|theanga}} {{IPA|/\u02c8ha\u014b\u0261\u0259/}} \"tongue\" (lenited)<br />{{lang|ga|theann}} {{IPA|/\u00e7a\u02d0n\u032a\u02e0/}} \"tight\" (lenited), {{lang|ga|theocht}} {{IPA|/\u00e7o\u02d0xt\u032a\u02e0/}} \"heat\" (lenited), {{lang|ga|thi\u00failip}} {{IPA|/\u02c8\u00e7u\u02d0l\u02b2\u0259p\u02b2/}} \"tulip\" (lenited), {{lang|ga|thiocfadh}} {{IPA|/\u02c8\u00e7\u028ak\u0259x/}} \"would come\", {{lang|ga|thiubh}} {{IPA|/\u00e7\u028aw/}} \"thick\" (lenited)\n|-\n| colspan=2 | Silent at the end of a syllable\n| {{lang|ga|bl\u00e1th}} {{IPA|/b\u02e0l\u032a\u02e0a\u02d0/}} \"blossom\", {{lang|ga|cith}} {{IPA|/c\u026a/}} \"shower\", {{lang|ga|cothrom}} {{IPA|/\u02c8k\u0254\u027e\u02e0\u0259m\u02e0/}} \"equal\"\n|-\n| colspan=3 |  See [[#Special pronunciations in verb forms|Special pronunciations in verb forms]] for '''-th-''' in verbal adjectives\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | '''ts'''<br /><small>(special lenition of '''s-''' after '''an''' 'the')</small>\n| broad\n| {{IPA|/t\u032a\u02e0/}}\n| {{lang|ga|an tsolais}} {{IPA|/\u0259n\u032a\u02e0 \u02c8t\u032a\u02e0\u0254l\u032a\u02e0\u0259\u0283/}} \"of the light\"\n|-\n| slender\n| {{IPA|/t\u02b2/}}; {{IPA|/t\u0255/}} in northern dialects\n| {{lang|ga|an tS\u00edn}} {{IPA|/\u0259n\u02b2 t\u02b2i\u02d0n\u02b2/}} \"China\"\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | '''v''' <small>(loan consonant)</small>\n| broad\n| {{IPA|/w/}}~{{IPA|/v\u02e0/}}\n| {{lang|ga|v\u00f3ta}} {{IPA|/\u02c8wo\u02d0t\u032a\u02e0\u0259/}} \"vote\"\n|-\n| slender\n| {{IPA|/v\u02b2/}}\n| {{lang|ga|veidhl\u00edn}} {{IPA|/\u02c8v\u02b2\u0259il\u02b2i\u02d0n\u02b2/}} \"violin\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |'''z''' <small>(loan consonant)</small>\n|broad\n|{{IPA|/z\u02e0/}}\n|{{lang|ga|z\u00fa}} {{IPA|/z\u02e0u\u02d0/}} \"zoo\"\n|-\n|slender\n|{{IPA|/\u0292/}}; {{IPA|/\u0291/}} in northern dialects\n|{{lang|ga|Zen}} {{IPA|/\u0292\u025bn\u02b2/}} \"Zen\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |'''zs''' <small>(uncommon representation of [[Cape Clear Island|Cape Clear]] eclipsis of '''s''')</small>\n|broad\n|{{IPA|/z\u02e0/}}\n|{{lang|ga|zsolas}} {{IPA|/z\u02e0\u0254l\u032a\u02e0\u0259s\u02e0/}} \"light\" (eclipsed)\n|-\n|slender\n|{{IPA|/\u0292/}}\n|{{lang|ga|zsean}} {{IPA|/\u0292an\u032a\u02e0/}} \"old\" (eclipsed)\n|}\n\n==Vowels==\nSequences of vowels are common in Irish spelling due to the \"{{lang|ga|caol le caol agus leathan le leathan}}\" (\"slender with slender and broad with broad\") rule. This rule states that the vowels on either side of any consonant must be both slender (''e'' or ''i'') or both broad (''a'', ''o'' or ''u''), to unambiguously determine the consonant's own broad vs. slender pronunciation.  \nAn apparent exception is the combination ''ae'', which is followed by a ''broad'' consonant despite the ''e''.\n\nIn spite of the complex chart below, pronunciation of vowels in Irish is mostly predictable from a few simple rules.\n\n* {{lang|ga|Fada}} vowels (''\u00e1'', ''\u00e9'', ''\u00ed'', ''\u00f3'', ''\u00fa'') are always pronounced.\n* Vowels on either side of a {{lang|ga|fada}} (except for other ''fada'' vowels) most often do not spell any [[phoneme]] (there are several exceptions).  Their presence is almost always necessary to simply satisfy the \"{{lang|ga|caol le caol agus leathan le leathan}}\" rule.  These letters are not entirely silent, however. The {{lang|ga|fada}} vowel and the adjacent consonant require the tongue body to be in different positions, and these letters capture the transient sound produced while it is moving from one position to the other.\n* Between a consonant and a broad vowel, ''e'' and ''i'' are usually non-phonemic in the same way.  This applies to:\n** The ''e'' in {{wikt-lang|ga|fear}}, {{wikt-lang|ga|bean}}, {{wikt-lang|ga|leabhar}}, {{wikt-lang|ga|seomra}}\n** The ''i'' in {{wikt-lang|ga|cailin}}, {{wikt-lang|ga|uncail}}, {{wikt-lang|ga|abhainn}}, {{wikt-lang|ga|aimsir}}, {{wikt-lang|ga|bainne}}, {{wikt-lang|ga|cois}}, {{wikt-lang|ga|fliuch}}\n** '''But''' the ''o'' in {{wikt-lang|ga|troim}}, {{wikt-lang|ga|roimh}}, {{wikt-lang|ga|fios}}, {{wikt-lang|ga|iolar}}, not the ''i''\n* The short vowels ''io'', ''oi'' and ''ui'' have multiple pronunciations that depend on adjacent consonants.\n\nThe following series of charts indicates how written vowels are ''generally'' pronounced.  Each dialect has certain divergences from this general scheme, and may also pronounce some words in a way that does not agree with standard orthography.\n\n===Simple vowels===\n\nUnstressed vowels are generally reduced to [[schwa]] ({{IPA|/\u0259/}}).\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=2 | Letter(s)\n! Phoneme\n! Examples\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | '''a'''\n| rowspan=2 | stressed\n| {{IPA|/a/}}\n| {{lang|ga|fan}} {{IPA|/f\u02e0an\u032a\u02e0/}} \"stay\" (imper.)\n|-\n| {{IPA|/a\u02d0/}} before '''rl, rn, rd'''<br />before syllable-final '''ll, nn, rr'''<br />before word-final '''m'''\n| {{lang|ga|tarl\u00fa}} {{IPA|/\u02c8t\u032a\u02e0a\u02d0\u027e\u02e0l\u032a\u02e0u\u02d0/}} \"happening\", {{lang|ga|carn\u00e1n}} {{IPA|/\u02c8ka\u02d0\u027e\u02e0n\u032a\u02e0a\u02d0n\u032a\u02e0/}} \"(small) heap\", {{lang|ga|garda}} {{IPA|/\u02c8\u0261a\u02d0\u027e\u02e0d\u032a\u02e0\u0259/}} \"policeman\"<br />{{lang|ga|mall}} {{IPA|/m\u02e0a\u02d0l\u032a\u02e0/}} \"slow, late\", {{lang|ga|ann}} {{IPA|/a\u02d0n\u032a\u02e0/}} \"there\", {{lang|ga|barr}} {{IPA|/b\u02e0a\u02d0\u027e\u02e0/}} \"tip, point\"<br />{{lang|ga|am}} {{IPA|/a\u02d0m\u02e0/}} \"time\"\n|-\n| unstressed\n| {{IPA|/\u0259/}}\n| {{lang|ga|\u00f3lann}} {{IPA|/\u02c8o\u02d0l\u032a\u02e0\u0259n\u032a\u02e0/}} \"drink\" (present), {{lang|ga|m\u00e1la}} {{IPA|/\u02c8m\u02e0a\u02d0l\u032a\u02e0\u0259/}} \"bag\"\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | '''e'''\n| stressed\n| {{IPA|/\u025b/}}\n| {{lang|ga|te}} {{IPA|/t\u02b2\u025b/}} \"hot\"\n|-\n| unstressed\n| {{IPA|/\u0259/}}\n| {{lang|ga|m\u00edle}} {{IPA|/\u02c8m\u02b2i\u02d0l\u02b2\u0259/}} \"thousand\"\n|-\n| rowspan=4 | '''i'''\n| rowspan=2 | stressed\n| {{IPA|/\u026a/}}\n| {{lang|ga|pic}} {{IPA|/p\u02b2\u026ac/}} \"pitch\", {{lang|ga|ifreann}} {{IPA|/\u02c8\u026af\u02b2\u027e\u02b2\u0259n\u032a\u02e0/}} \"hell\"\n|-\n| {{IPA|/i\u02d0/}} before syllable-final '''ll, nn'''<br />before word-final '''m'''\n| {{lang|ga|cill}} {{IPA|/ci\u02d0l\u02b2/}} \"church\", {{lang|ga|cinnte}} {{IPA|/\u02c8ci\u02d0n\u02b2t\u02b2\u0259/}} \"sure\"<br />{{lang|ga|im}} {{IPA|/i\u02d0m\u02b2/}} \"butter\"\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | unstressed\n| {{IPA|/\u0259/}}\n| {{lang|ga|faoistin}} {{IPA|/\u02c8f\u02e0i\u02d0\u0283t\u02b2\u0259n\u02b2/}} \"confession\"\n|-\n| {{IPA|/\u026a/}} finally\n| {{lang|ga|aici}} {{IPA|/\u02c8\u025bc\u026a/}} \"at her\"\n|-\n| rowspan=5 | '''o'''\n| rowspan=4 | stressed\n| {{IPA|/\u0254/}}\n| {{lang|ga|post}} {{IPA|/p\u02e0\u0254s\u02e0t\u032a\u02e0/}} \"post\"\n|-\n| {{IPA|/\u028a/}} before '''n, m'''\n| {{lang|ga|Donncha}} {{IPA|/\u02c8d\u032a\u02e0\u028an\u032a\u0259x\u0259/}} (man's name), {{lang|ga|crom\u00f3g}} {{IPA|/\u02c8k\u027e\u02e0\u028am\u02e0o\u02d0\u0261/}} \"hooked nose\"\n|-\n| {{IPA|/o\u02d0/}} before '''rl, rn, rd'''<br />before syllable-final '''ll, rr'''\n| {{lang|ga|bord}} {{IPA|/b\u02e0o\u02d0\u027e\u02e0d\u032a\u02e0/}} \"table\", {{lang|ga|orlach}} {{IPA|/\u02c8o\u02d0\u027e\u02e0l\u032a\u02e0\u0259x/}} \"inch\"<br />{{lang|ga|poll}} {{IPA|/p\u02e0o\u02d0l\u032a\u02e0/}} \"hole\", {{lang|ga|corr}} {{IPA|/ko\u02d0\u027e\u02e0/}} \"odd\"\n|-\n| {{IPA|/u\u02d0/}} before syllable-final '''nn'''<br />before word-final '''m, ng'''\n| {{lang|ga|fonn}} {{IPA|/f\u02e0u\u02d0n\u032a\u02e0/}} \"desire, inclination\"<br />{{lang|ga|trom}} {{IPA|/t\u032a\u02e0\u027e\u02e0u\u02d0m\u02e0/}} \"heavy\", {{lang|ga|long}} {{IPA|/l\u032a\u02e0u\u02d0\u014b\u0261/}} \"ship\"\n|-\n| unstressed\n| {{IPA|/\u0259/}}\n| {{lang|ga|mo}} {{IPA|/m\u02e0\u0259/}} \"my\", {{lang|ga|cothrom}} {{IPA|/\u02c8k\u0254\u027e\u02e0\u0259m\u02e0/}} \"equal\"\n|-\n| rowspan=5 | '''u'''\n| rowspan=3 | stressed\n| {{IPA|/\u028a/}}\n| {{lang|ga|dubh}} {{IPA|/d\u032a\u02e0\u028aw/}} \"black\"\n|-\n| {{IPA|/\u0254/}} in English loanwords, corresponds to {{IPA|/\u028c/}}\n| {{lang|ga|bus}} {{IPA|/b\u02e0\u0254s\u02e0/}}, {{lang|ga|club}} {{IPA|/kl\u032a\u02e0\u0254b\u02e0/}}\n|-\n| {{IPA|/u\u02d0/}} before '''rl, rn, rd'''\n| {{lang|ga|burla}} {{IPA|/\u02c8b\u02e0u\u02d0\u027e\u02e0l\u032a\u02e0\u0259/}} \"bundle\", {{lang|ga|murn\u00e1n}} {{IPA|/\u02c8m\u02e0u\u02d0\u027e\u02e0n\u032a\u02e0a\u02d0n\u032a\u02e0/}} \"ankle\", {{lang|ga|url\u00e1r}} {{IPA|/\u02c8u\u02d0\u027e\u02e0l\u032a\u02e0a\u02d0\u027e\u02e0/}} \"floor\"\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | unstressed\n| {{IPA|/\u0259/}}\n| {{lang|ga|agus}} {{IPA|/\u02c8a\u0261\u0259s\u02e0/}} \"and\"\n|-\n| {{IPA|/\u028a/}} finally\n| {{lang|ga|urthu}} {{IPA|/\u02c8\u028a\u027e\u02e0h\u028a/}} \"on them\"\n|}\n\n===Vowels with an apex accent===\n\nVowels with an [[apex (diacritic)|apex]] (known in Irish as a {{lang|ga|fada}} or {{lang|ga|s\u00edneadh fada}}) are always pronounced long. In [[digraph (orthography)|digraphs]] and [[trigraph (orthography)|trigraph]]s containing a vowel with an apex, only the vowel with the accent mark is usually pronounced, but there are several exceptions, for instance in trigraphs where the two letters without an accent are right next to one another rather than on either side of the accented vowel.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Letter(s)\n! Phoneme\n! Examples\n|-\n| '''\u00e1'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{IPA|/a\u02d0/}}\n| {{lang|ga|b\u00e1n}} {{IPA|/b\u02e0a\u02d0n\u032a\u02e0/}} \"white\"\n|-\n| '''\u00e1i'''\n| {{lang|ga|d\u00e1il}} {{IPA|/d\u032a\u02e0a\u02d0l\u02b2/}} \"assembly\", {{lang|ga|gabh\u00e1il}} {{IPA|/\u02c8\u0261awa\u02d0l\u02b2/}} \"taking\"\n|-\n| '''a\u00ed'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{IPA|/i\u02d0/}}\n| {{lang|ga|ma\u00edgh}} {{IPA|/m\u02e0i\u02d0j/}} \"claim\" (imper.), {{lang|ga|guta\u00ed}} {{IPA|/\u02c8\u0261\u028at\u032a\u02e0i\u02d0/}} \"vowels\"\n|-\n| '''a\u00edo'''\n| {{lang|ga|na\u00edon\u00e1n}} {{IPA|/\u02c8n\u032a\u02e0i\u02d0n\u032a\u02e0a\u02d0n\u032a\u02e0/}} \"infant\", {{lang|ga|beanna\u00edonn}} {{IPA|/\u02c8b\u02b2an\u032a\u02e0i\u02d0n\u032a\u02e0/}} \"blesses\"\n|-\n| '''ao\u00fa'''\n| {{IPA|/i\u02d0.u\u02d0/}}\n| {{lang|ga|nao\u00fa}} {{IPA|/\u02c8n\u032a\u02e0i\u02d0u\u02d0/}} \"ninth\"\n|-\n| '''\u00e9'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{IPA|/e\u02d0/}}\n| {{lang|ga|s\u00e9}} {{IPA|/\u0283e\u02d0/}} \"he\"\n|-\n| '''\u00e9a'''\n| {{lang|ga|d\u00e9anamh}} {{IPA|/\u02c8d\u02b2e\u02d0n\u032a\u02e0\u0259w/}} \"doing\", {{lang|ga|buid\u00e9al}} {{IPA|/\u02c8b\u02e0\u026ad\u02b2e\u02d0l\u032a\u02e0/}} \"bottle\"\n|-\n| '''e\u00e1'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{IPA|/a\u02d0/}}\n| {{lang|ga|Se\u00e1n}} {{IPA|/\u0283a\u02d0n\u032a\u02e0/}} \"John\", {{lang|ga|caisle\u00e1n}} {{IPA|/\u02c8ka\u0283l\u02b2a\u02d0n\u032a\u02e0/}} \"castle\"\n|-\n| '''e\u00e1i'''\n| {{lang|ga|me\u00e1in}} {{IPA|/m\u02b2a\u02d0n\u02b2/}} \"middles\", {{lang|ga|caisle\u00e1in}} {{IPA|/\u02c8ka\u0283l\u02b2a\u02d0n\u02b2/}} \"castles\"\n|-\n| '''\u00e9i'''\n| {{IPA|/e\u02d0/}}\n| {{lang|ga|sc\u00e9imh}} {{IPA|/\u0283ce\u02d0v\u02b2/}} \"beauty\", {{lang|ga|p\u00e1ip\u00e9ir}} {{IPA|/\u02c8p\u02e0a\u02d0p\u02b2e\u02d0\u027e\u02b2/}} \"papers\"\n|-\n| '''\u00ed'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{IPA|/i\u02d0/}}\n| {{lang|ga|gn\u00edmh}} {{IPA|/\u025fn\u02b2i\u02d0v\u02b2/}} \"act, deed\" (gen.), {{lang|ga|cail\u00edn}} {{IPA|/\u02c8kal\u02b2i\u02d0n\u02b2/}} 'girl'\n|-\n| '''\u00edo'''\n| {{lang|ga|s\u00edol}} {{IPA|/\u0283i\u02d0l\u032a\u02e0/}} \"seed\"\n|-\n| '''i\u00e1'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{IPA|/i\u02d0.a\u02d0/}}\n| {{lang|ga|bi\u00e1n}} {{IPA|/\u02c8b\u02b2i\u02d0a\u02d0n\u032a\u02e0/}} \"size\"\n|-\n| '''i\u00e1i'''\n| {{lang|ga|li\u00e1in}} {{